# Privacy Pi

**Privacy Pi** is a Raspberry Pi–based privacy toolkit developed as a collaborative academic project. It provides DNS-level ad blocking, firewall customization, and secure VPN tunneling to enhance personal internet privacy and security.

---

## 🔧 Features

- 🚫 DNS-based ad and tracker blocking
- 🔒 Secure VPN routing (WireGuard/OpenVPN)
- 🔥 Custom firewall rules (UFW/IPTables)
- 📊 Lightweight network activity logging
- 🧰 Modular and scriptable setup for Raspberry Pi

---

## 💡 My Contributions

This project was developed as part of a team of 3 students. I personally contributed:

- Configured and automated VPN integration using WireGuard
- Designed custom IPTables rules for selective traffic blocking
- Developed shell scripts for automated setup and service control
- Helped document the architecture and usage flow in the README

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- Raspberry Pi OS (Debian-based)
- Bash and Python scripting
- WireGuard/OpenVPN
- UFW/IPTables
- Git for version control

